00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:09,540
heart of God. He wants to know us intimately, and He wants to hear from you, friends of

228
00:18:09,540 --> 00:18:20,410
God. But you know, the sad thing is, across our land, Christians still don't pray. I think one

229
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:26,830
reason is that somewhere deep down in the lives of many Christians, they believe that still that

230
00:18:26,830 --> 00:18:36,500
God is somehow not interested in their lives. There's still an idea that God has so much else

231
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:43,850
to do, holding up the universe, taking care of the big catastrophes, that somehow, who

232
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:44,510
am I?

233
00:18:45,420 --> 00:18:50,360
What is my life in terms of how God sees me and the world?

234
00:18:52,260 --> 00:18:57,700
I think many think that, well, God's not interested in my mortgage or my disagreement with my

235
00:18:57,700 --> 00:19:03,340
co-workers or problems at school or my backache or whatever it is, on and on and on.

236
00:19:03,340 --> 00:19:08,680
Those things seem so unimportant in the big scheme of things.

237
00:19:10,980 --> 00:19:11,500
Friends.

238
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:15,160
God has called you friends.

239
00:19:16,340 --> 00:19:23,000
And when friends are truly friends, friends share the most intimate details of life.

240
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:27,160
It's the little things that friends share, don't they?

241
00:19:28,540 --> 00:19:33,340
And God has called us friends and wants us to communicate as friends

242
00:19:33,340 --> 00:19:43,560
The little things he's concerned about, they may be little, but in your life, they're big, aren't they?

243
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:47,740
And God is concerned about the issues of our lives.

244
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,340
Praise God for that.

245
00:19:51,890 --> 00:20:00,650
I think, friends, if we're going to pray, we're going to have to first start by realizing how much God loves you.

246
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:06,760
And if I can just speak one thing this morning, if you get nothing else out of all that's been said,

247
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:12,840
if you will leave this place with this reality that God deeply loves you

248
00:20:12,840 --> 00:20:18,630
and he wants to talk with you, that's what it's all about.

249
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:23,060
He loves you. He loves you.

250
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:25,870
And he wants to hear from you.

251
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:30,520
Prayer is communicating with God who calls us friends.

252
00:20:32,890 --> 00:20:37,720
Lord, teach us to pray. Teach us to pray.

253
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:45,440
Prayer number three is asking of God.

254
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:49,400
It's asking of God.

255
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:54,710
When you're a child in a healthy relationship with your parents, you ask them for things.

256
00:20:55,830 --> 00:20:57,170
You're dependent on them.

257
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:59,350
You need them, and thus you ask of them.

258
00:21:00,190 --> 00:21:02,950
And the same, friends, is true with our Heavenly Father.

259
00:21:03,590 --> 00:21:08,450
We can ask of Him, and He delights to give to us.

260
00:21:09,290 --> 00:21:12,350
The Bible says in Philippians 4, verse 6,

261
00:21:13,070 --> 00:21:18,920
Don't worry about anything, but in all your prayers, ask God for what you need,

262
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:23,250
always thanking Him with a thankful heart.

263
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:27,020
A thankful heart.

264
00:21:28,570 --> 00:21:30,210
Do you notice what it said, don't worry about anything?

265
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:37,890
I think worrying has become a national sport,

266
00:21:37,890 --> 00:21:46,280
and we're all contenders, 9.5, 9.9.

267
00:21:46,420 --> 00:21:49,180
We're all good at worrying, aren't we?

268
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,240
You're all shaking your heads.

269
00:21:52,420 --> 00:21:53,620
I'm talking to you, aren't I?

270
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:57,800
We're connecting here, and I'm there too.

271
00:21:59,620 --> 00:22:00,440
I should know better.

272
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:01,520
We all should know better.

273
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:05,540
The Bible says we're to quit worrying and commence praying.

274
00:22:07,010 --> 00:22:07,870
Quit worrying.

275
00:22:09,010 --> 00:22:09,710
Commence praying.

276
00:22:11,950 --> 00:22:16,450
We're to ask God for what we need and do it with a thankful heart.

277
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:25,120
Your relationship with God gets intimate, friends, when you start talking about your real life with Him.

278
00:22:26,170 --> 00:22:29,310
It's one thing to pray about the big issues in the world.

279
00:22:29,630 --> 00:22:32,890
It's one thing to pray about the obvious needs in the world.

280
00:22:33,190 --> 00:22:34,810
And yes, we should do that.

281
00:22:34,810 --> 00:22:41,270
But just like an intimate relationship, it's about the little things, the real issues, the real needs,

282
00:22:41,750 --> 00:22:43,790
the things you might even be embarrassed about,

283
00:22:44,110 --> 00:22:48,590
but the things that really occupy your mind, that we worry about,

284
00:22:48,590 --> 00:22:52,230
and that our stomachs tighten up in little balls all about.

285
00:22:53,110 --> 00:22:54,130
You know what I'm talking about.

286
00:22:54,990 --> 00:22:58,130
God is concerned about those things,

287
00:22:58,470 --> 00:23:02,430
and he wants us to ask for things.

288
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:10,000
Friends, the Bible is affirming that God's chosen method of meeting our needs

289
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:10,900
is through prayer.

290
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:16,700
We need to ask.

291
00:23:17,580 --> 00:23:19,160
We need to ask.

292
00:23:22,780 --> 00:23:24,740
When Brent and Ryan ask me for things,

293
00:23:27,590 --> 00:23:30,010
there's times when I, as a dad, say,

294
00:23:30,010 --> 00:23:37,000
you know, not good choice right now, but you know what, I'm a real softy, and by and large,

295
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:43,140
I give in, right? I know the difference between things that are not good, but you know what,

296
00:23:43,260 --> 00:23:51,100
because I selfishly love to give to them. It's a blessing for me, because I love to see the delight

297
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:59,250
in their eyes, when even if it's just gift of time spent playing Legos on the floor, I love to do

298
00:23:59,250 --> 00:24:06,380
that. And the Heavenly Father loves to give to His children. He loves to give to His children.

299
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:15,480
That's us. Friends. His children. We've got to ask. I also want to share that I've been

300
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:20,590
reading in the book of Acts in my own personal devotions, and something I'm really struck

301
00:24:20,590 --> 00:24:29,070
with is that how often miracles and power is demonstrated in the early church. It's

302
00:24:29,070 --> 00:24:33,130
almost like you could walk up to an early Christian in the early church in the book

303
00:24:33,130 --> 00:24:37,590
of Acts. It's almost like you could ask them, hey, how's it going today? And they'd say,

304
00:24:37,670 --> 00:24:43,420
well, business as usual. A couple miracles this morning. Praying for one more tonight.

305
00:24:43,620 --> 00:24:51,550
Expect that. You just get a sense that God is moving. And I've asked myself why. I think

306
00:24:51,550 --> 00:24:58,070
because they asked that God would move with power. They expected it. They knew that God

307
00:24:58,070 --> 00:25:00,030
was going to hear their prayers.

308
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:02,540
And they prayed expectantly

309
00:25:02,540 --> 00:25:05,380
and asked God for power for living

310
00:25:05,380 --> 00:25:08,240
and for the miraculous around them.

311
00:25:09,690 --> 00:25:13,010
And I'm afraid the American church doesn't ask

312
00:25:13,010 --> 00:25:16,770
for God to move in our lives.

313
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:21,900
I think Christians today live often with the right head knowledge

314
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:23,520
but with little power

315
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:28,780
because we simply don't ask for the Spirit to move.

316
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:32,380
We've got to ask.

317
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:37,900
The great pastor C.H. Spurgeon of London, England once said this.

318
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:38,500
I love this.

319
00:25:39,140 --> 00:25:44,180
He said, God never shuts his storehouses until you shut your mouth.

320
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:49,040
File that one away.

321
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,040
You have to ask.

322
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,860
Prayer is asking of God.

323
00:25:56,830 --> 00:26:00,250
To affirm this, Luke writes these words of Jesus.

324
00:26:00,850 --> 00:26:01,990
Chapter 11.

325
00:26:01,990 --> 00:26:10,900
Is there anyone among you who, if your child asks for a fish, will give a snake instead of a fish?

326
00:26:11,950 --> 00:26:15,450
Or if the child asks for an egg, will give a scorpion?

327
00:26:16,660 --> 00:26:20,780
If you then, who are evil, know how to give good gifts to your children,

328
00:26:21,500 --> 00:26:27,400
how much more will the Heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to those who ask Him?

329
00:26:28,780 --> 00:26:29,940
Oh, isn't that beautiful?

330
00:26:31,380 --> 00:26:32,780
He gives good gifts.

331
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:36,980
If as an imperfect dad, very imperfect,

332
00:26:37,620 --> 00:26:41,060
if I delight and know how to give gifts to my children,

333
00:26:41,060 --> 00:26:44,960
how much more does God, who is our perfect heavenly Father,

334
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:50,900
how much more does He want to give to us, His friends, and His children?

335
00:26:51,620 --> 00:26:58,740
God delights in giving requests in prayer, or for prayer, in prayer.

336
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:06,030
Another verse I'm struck with is Psalm 37, 4.

337
00:27:06,370 --> 00:27:15,780
The psalmist writes, delight yourself in the Lord and he will give you the desires of your heart.

338
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:17,660
Delight yourself in the Lord.

339
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:21,160
And friends, that's not a suggestion.

340
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:23,400
That's a command.

341
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:26,420
Delight yourself in the Lord.

342
00:27:26,740 --> 00:27:27,900
Enjoy the Lord.

343
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:32,300
If you're doing your best to let the Lord work in your life,

344
00:27:32,300 --> 00:27:39,080
If you're doing your best to seek him and read his word and pray and be a part of the things of God,

345
00:27:39,220 --> 00:27:44,760
if you're doing your best to let God's spirit work in the inner recesses of your heart and life,

346
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:51,970
then your desires aren't going to be wrong because you're so close to the heartbeat of God.

347
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:56,570
And he'll give you the desires of your heart.

348
00:27:58,620 --> 00:28:00,340
And so I've got two questions to ask.

349
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:03,680
Food for thought and for action.

350
00:28:05,290 --> 00:28:08,090
What are you lacking in your life?

351
00:28:08,350 --> 00:28:12,500
simply because you've never asked God for it?

352
00:28:15,540 --> 00:28:18,110
What are you lacking in your life

353
00:28:18,110 --> 00:28:22,810
simply because you have not asked God for whatever it is?

354
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:25,620
I want you to think about that.

355
00:28:29,070 --> 00:28:29,870
My second question is,

356
00:28:29,950 --> 00:28:31,930
what do you need to ask of God this morning

357
00:28:31,930 --> 00:28:33,450
before you leave today?

358
00:28:34,930 --> 00:28:39,150
What do you need to ask of God before the day is over

359
00:28:39,150 --> 00:28:41,050
and before you even leave today?

360
00:28:43,470 --> 00:28:45,770
Lord, teach us to pray.

361
00:28:51,180 --> 00:28:52,380
My last point this morning

362
00:28:52,380 --> 00:28:59,140
is that prayer is also cooperating with God.

363
00:29:00,180 --> 00:29:02,690
It's cooperating with God.

364
00:29:04,290 --> 00:29:07,470
And I think this one is really exciting to me

365
00:29:07,470 --> 00:29:12,530
because he realized that God has a plan and a purpose

366
00:29:12,530 --> 00:29:14,690
for what's happening here on earth.

367
00:29:14,690 --> 00:29:18,490
And that God has a plan as he's bringing the kingdom

368
00:29:18,490 --> 00:29:20,870
day by day to this earth.

369
00:29:22,180 --> 00:29:25,000
And for those of you that have read Experiencing God

370
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,220
or been through that material,

371
00:29:26,540 --> 00:29:30,720
you're going to remember that the overarching principle that we're studying there

372
00:29:30,720 --> 00:29:34,300
is we're to get in line with what God is already doing.

373
00:29:35,230 --> 00:29:39,830
The challenge for us as Christians is to find out what God is doing

374
00:29:39,830 --> 00:29:44,930
and get underneath and be a part of what He is doing in the world.

375
00:29:46,510 --> 00:29:48,510
And you get in touch with that plan.

376
00:29:49,690 --> 00:29:52,190
One of the primary ways is through prayer.

377
00:29:54,150 --> 00:30:00,940
Friends, when we pray, our hearts and our minds and our souls become transformed

378
00:30:00,940 --> 00:30:04,260
and brought into line with God's agenda.

379
00:30:04,860 --> 00:30:07,940
The more time you spend with God in prayer,

380
00:30:07,940 --> 00:30:13,100
the more your heartbeat is going to beat at the frequency of God's heartbeat.

381
00:30:15,140 --> 00:30:20,760
You will begin to think God's thoughts, and you will feel as God feels,

382
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:26,220
and you will discern things in life as God sees them

383
00:30:26,220 --> 00:30:28,840
because you've spent time with him

384
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:32,000
and you're now cooperating with what he's doing.

385
00:30:34,330 --> 00:30:37,750
Jesus taught his disciples to pray and said this, Matthew 6,

386
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:42,680
Our Father in heaven, may your name be honored.

387
00:30:43,180 --> 00:30:44,980
May your kingdom come.

388
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:50,600
May your will be done here on earth just as it is in heaven.

389
00:30:50,600 --> 00:30:55,130
your will, your kingdom.

390
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:59,600
The prayer is asking that they be a part

391
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:02,460
of what God is doing in the world.

392
00:31:03,430 --> 00:31:05,110
It's cooperating with God.

393
00:31:06,770 --> 00:31:08,970
When Jesus was in the Garden of Gethsemane

394
00:31:08,970 --> 00:31:11,690
wrestling with God's plan for his life,

395
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:14,530
for the ultimate purpose for which he came,

396
00:31:14,530 --> 00:31:17,710
that he would take away our sin by going to the cross

397
00:31:17,710 --> 00:31:21,260
as a sacrifice for human evil,

398
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:28,360
In prayer, Jesus is wrestling with the reality that the hour has come.

399
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:29,860
And he says to the Father,

400
00:31:30,020 --> 00:31:36,240
Father, if you are willing, please take this cup of suffering away from me.

401
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:40,680
Yet I want your will and not mine.

402
00:31:42,320 --> 00:31:47,140
In prayer, our agenda becomes God's agenda.

403
00:31:49,660 --> 00:31:52,360
In prayer, we are changed.

404
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:56,460
In prayer, God works in us.

405
00:31:57,580 --> 00:32:03,680
In prayer, the Holy Spirit shifts our priorities to reflect His.

406
00:32:06,060 --> 00:32:10,600
In prayer, we become caught up in God's plan.

407
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:20,580
And as we become more sensitive to what God is doing in us and in others,

408
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:26,650
we pray for them more effectively, more effectively.

409
00:32:26,650 --> 00:32:32,620
When you're praying for other people, you are cooperating with God.

410
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:38,200
We're teaming up with God to accomplish His purposes in the world.

411
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:44,540
And friends, I think one of the fun things about prayer is it's not limited by space and time.

412
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:51,360
Prayers today can be answered immediately, or those prayers might be answered in the future,

413
00:32:52,580 --> 00:32:54,340
and they're not limited by space.

414
00:32:55,450 --> 00:32:59,090
Prayers prayed from Fullerton, from North Orange County, California,

415
00:32:59,090 --> 00:33:04,610
can go all over this city, all over this nation, all over this planet.

416
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:14,080
It's better than a web page because you're really going there in prayer.

417
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:17,360
You can pray in Fullerton.

418
00:33:17,540 --> 00:33:21,540
It's like sending a rocket all the way to Washington, D.C.

419
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:25,280
You can have God affecting things all over the world.

420
00:33:25,280 --> 00:33:32,500
I can get up tomorrow morning and go into my study and pray for our missionaries in various parts of this planet,

421
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:37,740
and you could ask me what you've been doing, and I could say in all seriousness,

422
00:33:37,980 --> 00:33:44,450
I've been getting around to the Middle East, I've been going to Africa, I've been going to Asia,

423
00:33:44,730 --> 00:33:46,950
and I would be truthful in what I'm saying.

424
00:33:47,530 --> 00:33:54,290
Prayer gets us around the world and makes changes and affects things in this world.

425
00:33:54,930 --> 00:33:56,230
What a privilege you have.

426
00:33:59,420 --> 00:34:02,100
Some of you think that you can't do much now,

427
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:09,400
that now that your bodies are changing and you just don't have the energy to get out and do as much,

428
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:14,420
you may have been great servants in being around this place and doing a lot of things.

429
00:34:14,740 --> 00:34:20,620
And I realize it's difficult to make those shifts as we get older and as we age.

430
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:26,680
I do karate and I'm realizing I am not as young as I used to be.

431
00:34:26,680 --> 00:34:31,040
And that sounds crazy from a guy in his mid-30s, but you know what?

432
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:36,170
When I'm competing against a 15-year-old, he's limber as a rubber band.

433
00:34:37,170 --> 00:34:37,870
I am not.

434
00:34:38,830 --> 00:34:40,910
And I hurt the next day.

435
00:34:41,610 --> 00:34:42,370
Thank you, Mario.

436
00:34:44,580 --> 00:34:47,860
But I know, so we age, we change, things happen.

437
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:48,560
But you know what?

438
00:34:48,580 --> 00:34:54,880
As we're getting along in years, you can pray and you can accomplish more in prayer

439
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:58,800
than even if you came down here and did physical things.

440
00:34:59,480 --> 00:35:03,220
In fact, I would bet you're probably doing even more important things through prayer.

441
00:35:04,300 --> 00:35:07,420
Never let it be said that we retire from the kingdom work

442
00:35:07,420 --> 00:35:11,340
because in prayer you can accomplish much, says the Scripture.

443
00:35:12,260 --> 00:35:13,640
And never forget it.

444
00:35:14,580 --> 00:35:17,700
And your prayers can change things around the world

445
00:35:17,700 --> 00:35:22,180
from right in your bedroom or your den or in this sanctuary.

446
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:27,740
Prayer is effectual and prayer is cooperating with our God.

447
00:35:28,140 --> 00:35:29,420
What a privilege it is.

448
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:34,520
To wrap it up, let me just say this.

449
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:47,450
The prayer is depending on God, it's communicating with God, it's asking of God, and it's cooperating with God.

450
00:35:47,450 --> 00:35:58,040
It's a marvelous gift that we have in this incredible entity called prayer.

451
00:36:00,220 --> 00:36:04,280
And I'm just going to challenge us to take up that powerful tool

452
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:11,670
and may it change our lives and change the lives of this church

453
00:36:11,670 --> 00:36:16,710
and may it change the lives for those for whom we pray.

454
00:36:16,710 --> 00:36:27,940
May we take this arsenal seriously and use it as God intends for his glory and for his purposes.

455
00:36:28,580 --> 00:36:31,100
And so, friends, together, let us pray.

456
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:33,940
Lord, teach us to pray.

457
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:39,460
May we at Fullerton be faithful in learning how to pray.

458
00:36:40,790 --> 00:36:45,530
And not only just learning, Father, may we learn that we may apply.

459
00:36:45,530 --> 00:36:48,990
that we may be truly prayer warriors

460
00:36:48,990 --> 00:36:52,300
praying every day.

461
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:54,840
The Bible says to pray without ceasing.

462
00:36:55,080 --> 00:36:57,650
Father, may that be our heart.

463
00:36:58,680 --> 00:36:59,860
May that be our actions.

464
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:01,840
And I pray, Father,

465
00:37:01,900 --> 00:37:04,120
you take these words and these scriptures,

466
00:37:05,810 --> 00:37:07,790
that you conform it to the individual needs

467
00:37:07,790 --> 00:37:08,990
of each one of us today

468
00:37:08,990 --> 00:37:11,620
and that you begin growing us up

469
00:37:11,620 --> 00:37:12,780
to a new level in prayer.

470
00:37:14,620 --> 00:37:15,620
And so I pray, Father,

471
00:37:15,700 --> 00:37:17,820
for this congregation of delightful people

472
00:37:17,820 --> 00:37:20,680
that wherever they are in prayer today,

473
00:37:20,820 --> 00:37:22,280
that you take them to the next step,

474
00:37:23,470 --> 00:37:25,970
that you'd move them to a new place

475
00:37:25,970 --> 00:37:28,130
in believing prayer,

476
00:37:28,830 --> 00:37:31,610
in stepping out and praying for others,

477
00:37:32,860 --> 00:37:35,240
in just asking of you for their lives.

478
00:37:37,020 --> 00:37:40,340
And Father, your word says that much can be accomplished.

479
00:37:40,340 --> 00:37:44,160
I pray we would see dynamic changes in lives around us

480
00:37:44,160 --> 00:37:46,840
because this church continues to pray.

481
00:37:48,080 --> 00:37:50,740
So, Father, we ask that you bless us with your Holy Spirit,

482
00:37:50,840 --> 00:37:54,900
that we might pray according to what you would have for us to pray about,

483
00:37:55,460 --> 00:38:00,130
that we would truly be a cooperating church with you for the kingdom's sake,

484
00:38:00,630 --> 00:38:08,820
and we'd see many lives transformed because of the prayers offered in faith from this body.

485
00:38:10,850 --> 00:38:18,460
So do these things we ask, and we look forward to the testimony of what happens when we pray.

486
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:24,840
Father, I pray this morning that you also would come

487
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:27,140
and let those who may not know you yet

488
00:38:27,140 --> 00:38:29,480
know that they are loved

489
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:34,360
and that through Jesus Christ, they can be forgiven,

490
00:38:36,220 --> 00:38:38,240
that they can start fresh and new.

491
00:38:39,780 --> 00:38:40,820
And if there are any this morning

492
00:38:40,820 --> 00:38:43,660
that need to commit themselves to the Jesus Christ,

493
00:38:44,140 --> 00:38:47,260
to recommit or for the first time step out and say,

494
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:50,660
I need a new start, I need Jesus.

495
00:38:50,660 --> 00:38:54,900
I want to pray and have things happen

496
00:38:54,900 --> 00:38:58,680
because my Heavenly Father is there with me

497
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:01,840
if you're in that place today

498
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:03,560
you might pray something like this

499
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:06,690
Father I thank you

500
00:39:06,690 --> 00:39:10,510
that you sent Jesus to die for me

501
00:39:10,510 --> 00:39:11,510
in my place

502
00:39:11,510 --> 00:39:14,740
I know I've done wrong things

503
00:39:14,740 --> 00:39:15,780
I've gone my own way

504
00:39:15,780 --> 00:39:18,000
I've messed up my life

505
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:19,320
but I want a new start

506
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:20,300
I want fresh

507
00:39:20,300 --> 00:39:23,120
I want the Holy Spirit in me

508
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:25,170
and so I'm sorry

509
00:39:25,170 --> 00:39:27,980
the things I've done, the things I've said,

510
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:29,320
the things I've even thought.

511
00:39:31,300 --> 00:39:34,900
And I want it erased, that I may live fresh and new in you.

512
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:38,820
And as much as I understand today I'm going to live for you,

513
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:41,780
and I pray that you'd help me each day be faithful.

514
00:39:42,850 --> 00:39:47,380
My life is now yours, and I thank you for your grace.

515
00:39:48,020 --> 00:39:48,920
In Jesus' name.

516
00:39:52,170 --> 00:39:55,070
I invite you to stand this morning as we sing one more song together.

517
00:39:55,470 --> 00:40:02,130
And I'd like to say, if I've spoken to you...

